  <sect2 id="setuptools_scm" xreflabel="setuptools_scm-&setuptools_scm-version;">

    <title>Setuptools_scm-&setuptools_scm-version;</title>

    <indexterm zone="setuptools_scm">
      <primary sortas="a-setuptools_scm">setuptools_scm</primary>
    </indexterm>

    <sect3 role="package">
      <title>Introduction to Setuptools_scm Module</title>

      <para>
        The <application>Setuptools_scm</application> package is used to
        extract Python package versions from git or hg metadata instead
        of declaring them.
      </para>

      &lfs130_checked;

      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Package Information</bridgehead>
      <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
        <listitem>
          <para>
            下载地址（HTTP）：<ulink url="&setuptools_scm-download-http;"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            下载地址（FTP）：<ulink url="&setuptools_scm-download-ftp;"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            MD5 校验和：&setuptools_scm-md5sum;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            大小：&setuptools_scm-size;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            预计所需磁盘空间：&setuptools_scm-buildsize;
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            预计构建时间：&setuptools_scm-time;
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Setuptools_scm Dependencies</bridgehead>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect5">Required</bridgehead>
      <para role="required">
        <xref linkend="vcs_versioning"/>
      </para>

      <bridgehead renderas="sect5">Optional (for testing)</bridgehead>
      <para role="optional">
        <xref linkend="pypa-build"/>,
        <xref linkend="git"/>,
        <xref linkend="mercurial"/>,
        <xref linkend="pytest"/>,
        <xref linkend="sudo"/>,
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/pytest-timeout/">pytest-timeout</ulink>,
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/rich/">rich</ulink>,
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/ruff/">ruff</ulink>,
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/mypy/">mypy</ulink>,
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/griffe/">griffe</ulink>, and
        <ulink url="https://pypi.org/project/flake8/">flake8</ulink>
      </para>

    </sect3>

    <sect3 role="installation">
      <title>Installation of Setuptools_scm</title>

    <para>Build the module: </para>

&build-wheel; 

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>&install-wheel; setuptools_scm</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      To test the installation, make sure <xref linkend='pytest'/> and
      the other optional dependencies are
      installed and run (<literal>HOME=</literal> prevents the
      <filename>.gitconfig</filename> file in the home directory from
      interfering the tests):
    </para>

<screen remap="test"><userinput>python3 -m venv --system-site-packages testenv &amp;&amp;
testenv/bin/pip3 install --group test          &amp;&amp;
TZ=UTC HOME= testenv/bin/python3 -m pytest</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If <xref linkend='git'/> and/or <xref linkend='mercurial'/> are not
      installed, the tests depending on the missing one(s) will be skipped.
      Some tests may invoke <xref linkend='sudo'/> and request a password.
    </para>

    </sect3>

